Detailed Description

A simple CHStack implemented using a CHSinglyLinkedList.

This implementation uses a CHSinglyLinkedList, since it's slightly faster than using a CHDoublyLinkedList, and requires a little less memory.

A singly-linked list is a natural choice since objects are only inserted and removed at the top of the stack, which is easily modeled as the head of a linked list. Enumerating from the top of the stack to the bottom also follows the natural ordering of a linked list.

Also, since it's a stack, it's unlikely that there is any need to enumerate over the object from bottom to top.

- (BOOL) isEqualToStack: (id< CHStack >)  otherStack [implementation]

Compares the receiving stack to another stack.

Two stacks have equal contents if they each hold the same number of objects and objects at a given position in each stack satisfy the -isEqual: test.

Parameters:
otherStackA stack.
Returns:
YES if the contents of otherStack are equal to the contents of the receiver, otherwise NO.

- (NSEnumerator*) objectEnumerator

Returns an enumerator that accesses each object in the stack from top to bottom.

Returns:
An enumerator that accesses each object in the stack from top to bottom. The enumerator returned is never nil; if the stack is empty, the enumerator will always return nil for -nextObject and an empty array for -allObjects.
Attention:
The enumerator retains the collection. Once all objects in the enumerator have been consumed, the collection is released.
Warning:
Modifying a collection while it is being enumerated is unsafe, and may cause a mutation exception to be raised.
See also:
- allObjects
- (NSArray*) objectsAtIndexes: (NSIndexSet *)  indexes

Returns an array containing the objects in the receiver at the indexes specified by a given index set.

Parameters:
indexesA set of positions corresponding to objects to retrieve from the receiver.
Returns:
A new array containing the objects in the receiver specified by indexes.
Exceptions:
NSRangeExceptionif any location in indexes exceeds the bounds of the receiver.
NSInvalidArgumentExceptionif indexes is nil.
Attention:
To retrieve objects in a given NSRange, pass [NSIndexSet indexSetWithIndexesInRange:range] as the parameter to this method.
